    "created_at": "2015-09-03T20:07:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-03T20:08:13Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The sheer number of trees stresses some of the slower parts of the engine:\n- Trees are frozen under fog. This means that they all have to be constantly tracked to see if they're within the sight range of the player. Each player has a different view of the map, so this gets slower just by adding more players. \n- The radar needs to constantly track every actor which should be showing up on it.\n- The number of actors make our sync checks slow - because there's more stuff to check to make sure it's all in sync.\n\nSome of my immediate musings to improve each of these are:\n- For permanent and unchanging features of the map - we should avoid making them freezeable somehow - if they can't possibly change when moving it or out of the sight of the player then we can avoid the checks to see if they're in range.\n- There are probably some things we can do to improve the speed of the radar generally.\n- If trees weren't freezeable that would make sync checks a bit faster since we wouldn't need to check their frozen state was in sync.\n\nNot necessarily saying these are possible, just thinking out loud here.\n"
  },
