    "updated_at": "2015-09-04T05:06:35Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Maybe we should make a class for objects that there are a lot of that don't hugely contribute to the gameplay and thus can have extremely reduced functionality, but can easily be replaced with a proper actor when the needs arises (TerrainOverlay or similar). All you'd need to broadcast about them would be their creation and their destruction. Perhaps we could implement some sort of caching system for the radar that initially generates the overlay for all objects of that class and removes them when they're destroyed or adds them when they're created. Does any of this seem like a workable idea?\n"
